        <h2 id="post-449"><a href="http://ajaxian.com/archives/moofx-more-effects-built-on-prototype" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Moo.fx: More effects. Built on Prototype">Moo.fx: More effects. Built on Prototype</a></h2>
        <p class="meta">Category:  <a href="http://ajaxian.com/by/topic/prototype" title="View all posts in Prototype" rel="category tag">Prototype</a>,  <a href="http://ajaxian.com/by/topic/toolkit" title="View all posts in Toolkit" rel="category tag">Toolkit</a></p>
        <p><a href="http://moofx.mad4milk.net/">moo.fx</a> is a superlightweight, ultratiny, megasmall javascript effects library, written with <a href="http://prototype.conio.net/">prototype.js</a> by Valerio Proietti.</p>
<p>This beast weighs in at a massive 3kb :)</p>
<p>Prototype seems to be one of those libraries that people just want to build on. And this one gives you effects such as:</p>
<ul>
<li>Toggle Opactiy</li>
<li>Toggle Height</li>
<li>Toggle Width</li>
<li>FadeSize Width, Height, Both</li>
<li>Toggle Resize</li>
<li>Custom Resize</li>
<li>Text Transition</li>
</ul>
<h3>To make this happen&#8230;</h3>
<blockquote><pre>
 window.onload = function(){
 var effect = new fx.Height('myelement',{duration:400,
  onComplete: function(){
   alert('the effect is finished');
  }
 });
}
</pre>
</blockquote>
<h3>Info</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://moofx.mad4milk.net/">Home page</a></li>
<li><a href="http://moofx.mad4milk.net/tests.html">Demo test page</a></li>
<li><a href="http://moofx.mad4milk.net/moofx.zip">Full download</a></li>
<li><a href="http://moofx.mad4milk.net/moo.fx.js">To see how simple and clean</a></li>
</ul>
<p><a href="http://moofx.mad4milk.net/tests.html"><img alt="moo.fx" src="http://www.ajaxian.com/archives/moofx.png" width="640" height="218" border="0" /></a></p>
<p>( via <a href="http://www.robsanheim.com/2005/10/26/moofx-lightweight-javascript-effects-built-on-prototype/">Rob Sanheim</a> )</p>
        
